<!--
<!DOCTYPE Settings [
<!ELEMENT Settings (Defaults,DivXs,Rtsps,Https)>
<!ELEMENT Defaults (Setting*)>
<!ELEMENT DivXs (Setting*)>
<!ELEMENT Rtsps (Setting*)>
<!ELEMENT Https (Setting*)>
<!ELEMENT Setting (Type*,Quirk*)>
<!ATTLIST Setting name CDATA #REQUIRED>
<!ATTLIST Setting type CDATA>
<!ELEMENT Type EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST Type name CDATA #REQUIRED>
<!ELEMENT Quirk EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST Quirk name CDATA #REQUIRED>
]>

There's a simple and a complex syntax to declare the availability of a
media codec:

A codec that properly follows the OpenMax spec and therefore doesn't have any
quirks and that only supports a single content type can be declared like so:

    <MediaPlayer name="OMX.foo.bar" type="something/interesting" />

If a codec has quirks OR supports multiple content types, the following syntax
can be used:

    <MediaPlayer name="OMX.foo.bar" >
        <Type name="something/interesting" />
        <Type name="something/else" />
        ...
        <Quirk name="requires-allocate-on-input-ports" />
        <Quirk name="requires-allocate-on-output-ports" />
        <Quirk name="output-buffers-are-unreadable" />
    </MediaPlayer>

Only the three quirks included above are recognized at this point:

"requires-allocate-on-input-ports"
    must be advertised if the component does not properly support specification
    of input buffers using the OMX_UseBuffer(...) API but instead requires
    OMX_AllocateBuffer to be used.

"requires-allocate-on-output-ports"
    must be advertised if the component does not properly support specification
    of output buffers using the OMX_UseBuffer(...) API but instead requires
    OMX_AllocateBuffer to be used.

"output-buffers-are-unreadable"
    must be advertised if the emitted output buffers of a decoder component
    are not readable, i.e. use a custom format even though abusing one of
    the official OMX colorspace constants.
    Clients of such Local will not be able to access the decoded data,
    naturally making the component much less useful. The only use for
    a component with this quirk is to render the output to the screen.
    Audio Local MUST NOT advertise this quirk.
    Video Local that advertise this quirk must be accompanied by a
    corresponding color space converter for thumbnail extraction,
    matching surfaceflinger support that can render the custom format to
    a texture and possibly other code, so just DON'T USE THIS QUIRK.

-->

<Settings>
    <Defaults>
    	<Setting key="Video:MaxWidth" value="1920" />
    	<Setting key="Video:MaxHeight" value="1080" />
    	<Setting key="P-frame:Seek" value="false" />			<!-- 'true' uses P-frame seek function, I-project uses I-frame seek only.('false'). -->
    	<Setting key="LandScape:Only" value="false" />			<!-- If 'false' switches width and height when the rotation degree is 90, 270. -->
																<!-- Set 'true' when default video apk supports landscape-mode only -->
    </Defaults>

    <DivXs>
    	<Setting key="Video:MaxWidth" value="1920" />
    	<Setting key="Video:MaxHeight" value="1080" />
    	<Setting key="Support:DivX" value="true" />  			<!-- If 'true' supports DivX contents. -->
    </DivXs>

    <Rtsps>
		<Setting key="UserAgent:Default" value="Player/LG Player 1.0 for Android(stagefright alternative)" />
		<Setting key="UserAgent:Version" value="false" />		<!-- use: true, not use: false -->
																<!--	false : "Player/LG Player 1.0"("Player/LG Player 1.0") -->
																<!--	true : "LG-V909/V07k Player/LG Player 1.0"("Model i/version i Player/LG Player 1.0") -->
		<Setting key="Port:Min" value="0" />					<!-- # of min-port, AT&T uses 6970, Others use 0 which means no limit. -->
		<Setting key="Port:Max" value="0" />					<!-- # of max-port, AT&T uses 32000, Others use 0 which means no limit.-->
		<Setting key="ProbePacket:send" value="SendMode1" />	<!-- Starhub uses 'SendMode1'. Singtel uses 'SendMode2'. 'SendMode1' not use this feature(default value). -->
		<Setting key="InitBuffering:Duration" value="0" />		<!-- msec, 0 means using default value which depends on player engine, HongKong-Hutchinson/PCCW uses 5000. -->
		<Setting key="ReBuffering:Duration" value="0" />		<!-- msec, 0 means using default value which depends on player engine, HongKong-Hutchinson/PCCW uses 10000. -->
		<Setting key="Skip:PauseResume" value="false" />		<!-- Whether disables pause and resume while RTSP streaming, Only ES-TLF/AU-TEL uses 'true' others use 'false'. -->
		<Setting key="RTPoverTCP:Preferred" value="false" />	<!-- Whether RTPoverTCP preferred while RTSP streraming. -->
		<Setting key="RTPoverUDP:withWIFI" value="false" />	<!-- Whether use RTPoverUDP while RTSP streraming with WiFi. -->
		<Setting key="CIQ:Enable" value="false" />				<!-- NOT IMPL, Whether uses Sprint CIQ, Sprint uses 'true', others use 'false'. -->
		<Setting key="H264:EnforceSW" value="false" />			<!-- Whether uses s/w codec while h264 rtsp streaming. Only HongKong-PCCW uses 'true', others use 'false'. -->
		<Setting key="Default:CharacterSet" value="EUC-KR" />	<!-- CharacterSet ('EUC-KR', 'shift-jis', ...). -->
		<Setting key="Wrap:ErrorCode" value="false" />			<!-- if 'true', wraps error code which defined by LGU+. LGU+ uses 'true', others use 'false'. -->
    </Rtsps>

    <Https>
    	<Setting key="Streaming:PowerSave" value="true" />     <!-- If 'true' enables power-saving-mode while YouTube playing. -->
    </Https>

    <NoUseMimetypes>
    	<Setting key="NOUSE:MIME:1" value="video/mpeg2" />
    	<Setting key="NOUSE:MIME:2" value="audio/dts" />
    	<Setting key="NOUSE:MIME:3" value="audio/dts-lbr" />
    	<Setting key="NOUSE:MIME:4" value="aaa/bbb" />
    </NoUseMimetypes>

    <Features>
		<Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer" value="true" />
        <Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer:Version" value="2" />
        <Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer:Parameter" value="8.0" />
        <Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer:Limiter:Thresh" value="13500" />
        <Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer:Limiter:Slope" value="1.0" />
        <Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer:Compressor:Thresh" value="4000" />
        <Setting key="AudioEffect:SoundNormalizer:Compressor:Slope" value="0.42" />
    </Features>

</Settings>
